column9: A highlight of this experience for me was checking my campaign page everyday and seeing the number go up and up.
column10: A very significant moment for me was when I reached $1000. It was just a surreal moment and that's when it actually hit me that what I am doing is making a change.
column11: It was really surprising to me to see that people can be so generous and that anyone no matter how young can change the world.
column13: I don't really know what my theme song would be. Maybe who let the dogs out?
column14: In five years when I look back on this experience I will remember that I was almost 13 and I did such a great thing.
column15: I learned that the worst someone can say is no and that anything is possible.
column16: I raised over $1000 and I made a difference in people's and animal's lives.
column17: I wish that someone would ask me if they could do this, and if someone saw me as an inspiration to do something great.
column18: I am going to take on the challenges that come at me and I will always be a philanthropist. I hope to do something like this again in the near future.
column19: Putting it all together I would say 1-2 hours at most.
column20: My event was 2 hours so there's that and there were other mechanics so maybe 5 hours in total.
column21: I really loved that there was a place I could track my progress and one place people could find anything about the project. I can't think of anything for you to improve.
column22: This was a really fantastic experience and I hope everyone gets the chance to do something like this.  Thank you!
